      <Meanings>
        <Meaning id="afb2ac45-6410-4993-8be0-da99d4ae1698" type="Noun">
          <Vi>glucozơ</Vi>
          <En>A simple sugar (monosaccharide) that is a primary source of energy for living cells, especially in the human body; blood sugar.</En>
          <Example>People with diabetes must carefully monitor their blood glucose levels.</Example>
          <IsArchaic>false</IsArchaic>
          <Situations>
            <Situation id="acdae92a-aee3-4570-8055-066e97fdc107">
              <Vi>Một chỉ số y tế quan trọng trong chẩn đoán và theo dõi bệnh tiểu đường.</Vi>
              <En>An essential clinical marker used in diagnosing and managing diabetes.</En>
            </Situation>
            <Situation id="0cb5e62d-467e-46e1-933a-c5daba576358">
              <Vi>Thức ăn chứa carbohydrate được cơ thể chuyển hóa thành glucose để cung cấp năng lượng.</Vi>
              <En>Carbohydrate-rich foods are broken down into glucose to provide energy for the body.</En>
            </Situation>
          </Situations>
